canExecute(uint256).details: Reverts if the proposal with the given `_proposalId` does not exist.

params._endDate: The end date of the proposal.
params._startDate: The start date of the proposal.

returns._0: The address of the implementation contract.

params._maci: The address of the maci contract.
params._vkRegistry: The address of the vk registry.

returns._0: The minimum voting power required to create a proposal.

protocolVersion().details: This version number is not to be confused with the `release` and `build` numbers found in the `Version.Tag` struct inside the `PluginRepo` contract being used to version plugin setup and associated plugin implementation contracts.

returns._0: Returns the semantic Aragon OSx protocol version number.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate that the this implementation remains valid after an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

returns._0: Returns `true` if the interface is supported.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

STATE_TREE_DEPTH().notice: determines the capacity of the state tree

UPGRADE_PLUGIN_PERMISSION_ID().notice: The ID of the permission required to call the `_authorizeUpgrade` function.
